                            <comment id="12934896" author="dobes_vandermeer" created="Tue, 23 Nov 2010 17:01:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This also affects the use of FormParam where no message body (and no content type) is provided; if the default values of the parameters are enough for the method, people might expect to be able to POST with no entity and get a response instead of an error 500.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12935419" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Wed, 24 Nov 2010 17:51:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think in the early days I was checking for null because I was lazy specifying the media type in tests &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;, MediaType is guaranteed not to be null by the earlier code - but I&apos;ve added the suggested guard nonetheless - thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
